  "prompt": "What did you do before a day before JEE advanced?",
  "response": "The day before JEE Advanced is crucial for ensuring you're mentally and physically prepared for the exam. Here's what I or any dedicated student might typically do:\n\n### 1. **Review Key Concepts and Formulas**  \n   - Go through important formulas, concepts, and shortcuts in Physics, Chemistry, and Mathematics.  \n   - Focus on high-weightage topics and areas you\u2019re confident in.  \n\n### 2. **Practice Mock Tests or Previous Years' Papers**  \n   - Solve a mock test or a previous year\u2019s paper under timed conditions to simulate the exam environment.  \n   - Analyze mistakes and revise accordingly.  \n\n### 3. **Organize Exam Essentials**  \n   - Keep your admit card, ID proof, and other required documents ready.  \n   - Prepare a bag with necessary items like pens, pencils, erasers, water bottle, and snacks.  \n\n### 4. **Avoid Overloading**  \n   - Don\u2019t try to learn new topics or cram. Focus on strengthening what you already know.  \n\n### 5. **Relax and Stay Positive**  \n   - Engage in light activities like listening to music, taking a walk, or meditating to stay calm.  \n   - Avoid negative thoughts or discussions.  \n\n### 6. **Get Enough Sleep**  \n   - Ensure you get a good night\u2019s sleep (7\u20138 hours) to stay fresh and alert on the exam day.  \n\n### 7. **Plan for the Exam Day**  \n   - Plan your travel route to the exam center, considering possible delays.  \n   - Set an alarm to wake up early and have a healthy breakfast.  \n\nRemember, confidence and a positive mindset are key to performing well in JEE Advanced. All the best!",
